commit.message: Add multiples() function
Add powertower() function; Add recursive depth limit to avoid running out of stack memory (causing segfault)
Fixes for help in qalc and man page (issue #638)
Add support for solving equation with if() function using vectors of conditions and expressions
Fix awg(x)=... and awgd(x)=... when default assumption type is not real and fix solve() with these equations (issue #637)
Solve equations containing if() function (issue #636)
Support integer factorization of integers in matrix/vector, and of numerator and denominator in rational number (issue #635)
Fix setbits() (issue #615)
ABI of version 5.0.0 is incompatible with previous version (bump soversion, issue #633)

Replace special colorize values, for selection of Unicode exponents, with different use_unicode_signs values; Use Unicode exponents if format is false, even if tagtype is not TAG_TYPE_TERMINAL; Use Unicode exponents for scientific notation; Fix Unicode exponents with number bases < 10; Improve output of x+/-y with rounding up or down; Do not apply "read precision" setting to exponents for values with units; Change from line to point (or dot) plot style for data with many discontinuous points

Fix rounding of rational number for ROUNDING_HALF* other than ROUNDING_HALF_AWAY_FROM_ZERO; Enable spelling error detection when limit implicit multiplication is active; Do not interpret number in time format in incomplete expression (e.g. "5:24 * ") as sequence of numbers; Update exchange rates

commit.message: Improve parsing of text arguments; Do not replace quoted curly brackets in expression unless necessary; Improve parsing of "where" statements before expression; Improve/fix output in some corner cases; Do not use sexagesimal output format for very large numbers (when scientific notation is necessary for integer part) and reduce maximal number of decimals (for last position when previous positions is non-zero); Improve display of parsed hexadecimal floating-point literals using 0x...p... notation with negative exponent; Fix parsing of j:i:k syntax in some cases; Count Unicode symbols as one character in len() function; Support vectors in arguments for colon(); Handle case when initial guess results in division by zero, and avoid unnecessary error messages, in newtonsolve(); Fix "to decimals" in qalc; Improve support for new rounding methods in qalc; Declare Calculator functions ...NameIsValid and convertToValid...Name as const; Move some function declarations to avoid use of extern declarations in GUIs; Remove superfluous function variants; Increment version number; Update translations

Fix BTC exchange rate from coinbase, if available from other source, not used before restart after exchange rates update, and do not mark BTC as hidden (places the unit in submenu in GUIs) (issue #290);

Add support "where" statements, without "where", before main expression, e.g. "a=2, b=3; a^b" (related to issue #622); Fixes/improvements to handling of "where" expression; Fixes to detection of potential spelling mistakes

Change handling of "where" expression (create temporary variables) to allow previously undefined variable names and to avoid confusing output of parsed expression (e.g. redefined "c" displayed as SpeedOfLight)
Improvements to detection of spelling errors; Detect spelling errors in qalc options (when using set command)

Change handling a vectors in multiple function arguments (of non-vector type) - return vector instead of matrix, require equal number of elements, and use the same vector index for all argument for each function instance (e.g. atan2([1  2], [3  4]) = [atan2(1, 3)  atan(2 4)]; Set handle vector property by default, for text, date, and boolean arguments, and for arguments, in global non-builtin functions, without specified type; Enable parsing of vectors for text arguments; Add foreach() (simplified for function, using vector instead of counter); Add setbits() function; Change bitset() and digitset() to return vector when argument contain vector, instead if changing multiple positions; Add flip() function (changes order of elements in vectors and matrices); Add "binary bits" option in qalc; Change short name for "exp display" to "edisp" ("exp" can still be used but does not interpret a value of 10 the same); Improvements to scientific notation; EXP_BASE10 -> EXP_POWER_OF_10; Minor fixes

Add integerDigits(), digitGet(), and digitSet() functions; Add more rounding methods and replace PrintOptions::round_halfway_to_even (and truncate time zone value hack) with PrintOptions::rounding; Add PrintOptions::duodecimal_symbols (replace time zone value hack); Replace PrintOptions::lower_case_e with PrintOptions::exp_display and add option for scientific notation without E (10^x); Add ParseOptions::binary_bits (replaces non-boolean values for twos_complement and hexadecimal_twos_complement); Add keep command, which makes variable or function non-temporary, to qalc; Improve handling of "..."; Add private objects (empty for now) to MathStructure and ExpressionItem; Make minor changes which are now feasible because of binary compatibility breakage;
Add LightSecond, LightMinute, and LightHour units
Remove possibility to set multiple bits using a value > 1 (issue #615)
Set multiple bits in bitset() using a value > 1 or a vector of values (issue #615)
Add missing options and fix default values in man page (issue #619)

Show error messages for command without argument, if not a reasonable expression, even if "/" is not used; Check for potential spelling mistakes in unknown commands in qalc; Add support for values > 1 for twosin and hextwosin options in qalc; Update colon() title and description for getbit() and setbit(); Add support for "prefix" conversion option for "to" without expression in qalc; Add example for new syntax for sequence vector; Update translations; Update man page; Update ChangeLog
Add support for hexadecimal floating-point literals using 0x...p... notation (0x1.4p3 = 0x1.4 * 2^3 = 10)

In dsolve(), assume that C is real if y is (fixes dsolve(diff(y, x) = y)), and, if y cannot be isolated completely, return resulting equation in solve() function (e.g. dsolve(diff(y , x) = y)= solve(ln(y) = x + C, y)) (issue #617)

Add support for a...b syntax for sequence (vector) of integers; Add support for j:k (for sequence of numbers with increment 1), and j:i:k (with increment i) syntax; Add colon() function (used by new syntax); Improve bitget() and bitset(); Improve detection of spelling errors (only test for unit names if the unit placement in expression seems reasonable); Fix parentheses for numbers (with scientific notation)

Do not list reactivated global objects when using "list" command (without argument); Recognize function name with parentheses appended in argument of "delete" command (useful for deletion of function with same name as variable or unit) (issue #616)
Add bitset() and bitget() functions (issue #615)
